  "time_ut": 1656934386,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0da2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca - \u0db8\u0ddb\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A friendly meeting between Sajith and Maitri",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Leader of the Opposition Sajith Premadasa, former President Maithripala Sirisena and a group of political party representatives and civil society activists met today at the office of the Leader of the Opposition and engaged in a special discussion.",
        "This was held as a crucial meeting in the program of \"National Reform and Forward Movement\" to rebuild the country, which has fallen into serious disrepair.",
        "The leader of the opposition who spoke there said that in the past 3 years, the rulers of this country have not listened to what other people have to say and think that they are the only ones who are right.",
        "In order to get rid of it, everyone should come together and go for social, economic and political reform, the opposition leader said.",
        "The opposition leader also said that the country can be built through a social reform that listens to everyone's opinions without dictatorship, so the proposals and ideas of the progressive parties will be listened to.",
        "The opposition leader further said that the aim of the opposition is to rebuild the country through a common national agenda that can bring together the diversified ideas and through that agenda the lost breath of the people of the country can be given again.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena, who attended the event, said that the Sri Lanka Freedom Party will give full support to the \"National Reform and Forward Journey\" programme.",
        "The former president also said that in order to build the country strong, we should resort to a constitutional reform program that did not exist before.",
        "Mr. Sirisena mentioned that friendly countries like Japan are far away from Sri Lanka and the current government is responsible for that.",
        "The former president further said that because the people involved in the struggle and the youth community think about the country in a more democratic way, everyone should think about a new government that will make their dreams come true.",
        "Samagi Jana Balawega General Secretary Ranjith Maddumabandara, President Sarath Fonseka, National Organizer Tissa Attanayake, Dr. Rajitha Senaratne, Mano Ganesan, Rauf Hakeem, P. Digambaram, many political leaders and a large number of civil activists including senior journalist Victor Ivan, Gamini Viyangoda, Rohan Samarajeeva also participated in this event."
      ],
